**User Story: Soccer Manager API Development**

**Title**: Develop RESTful API for Soccer Manager Application

**As a** football fan,  **I want** to create fantasy teams and buy or sell players via a RESTful API,  
**So that** I can engage in managing my own football team.

**Acceptance Criteria**:

- **Platform**: Implement using the **latest version of the Go Project**.
- **Authorization**: Develop an authorization system.
- **Database**: Create a database architecture.
- **User Account Management**:
  - Users must be able to create an account and log in using the API.
  - Each user can have **only one team**
- **Team Creation**:
  - Upon user signup, automatically assign a team of **20 players**, consisting of:
    - **3 goalkeepers**
    - **6 defenders**
    - **6 midfielders**
    - **5 attackers**
  - Each player has an **initial value of $1,000,000**.
  - Each team has an additional budget of **$5,000,000** to purchase players.
- **Team Information**:
  - Users can view their team and player information.
  - Team details include:
    - Team name and country (editable)
    - Total team value (sum of player values)
- **Player Information**:
  - Players have the following attributes:
    - First name, last name, country (editable by team owner)
    - Age (randomly generated between 18 and 40) and market value
- **Transfer List Functionality**:
  - Team owners can set players on a transfer list with an asking price.
  - Once a player is listed, the asking price must be displayed on a market list.
  - Upon purchase, the player must be bought for the listed price.
  - Users can view all players on the transfer list.
  - Team budgets must be updated with each transfer.
  - When a player is transferred, their value should increase by **10% to 100%** with a random factor applied.
- **API Functionality**: Ensure all user actions can be performed via RESTful API, including authentication.

**Additional Notes**:
- Postman collection must be provided
- Project must be uploaded to github as a public repository
- Unit tests are not required but are recommended.
- The application must support localization in **English and Georgian**.